cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI

This paper deals with word embeddings and their biases, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses methods for measuring and removing biases, which are related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also presents a new measure of association, which involves statistical analysis, making cs.CY (Computational Geometry) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of a common association test for word embeddings, which is related to statistics and hypothesis testing, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category as well.
